Popular Nollywood actors have openly drummed support for the standard bearer of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, in the 2023 presidential elections. In a now-viral one minute-thirteen seconds video clip seen by The Nation, the League of Actors comprising Fausat Balogun, Yinka Quadri, Jide Kosoko, Taiwo Hassan, Faithia Williams, Femi Adebayo, Shola Kosoko, Saheed Balogun, among others were seen campaigning for Tinubu. Although the video has elicited mixed reactions from fans across several social media platforms, the actors who assured Tinubu of their support in the video claimed that the former governor of Lagos State made acting and politics interesting by influencing many actors to venture into politics.   5 die, nine injured in Lagos-Ibadan road crash     Inmate graduates with 2nd Class Upper from Open University     Two shot dead, 16 abducted in Kaduna   One of the actors Yinka Quadri on his Instagram page said: “I, Alhaji Olayinka Quadri pledge my full support for BAT not because I was paid to do so but because of Asiwaju’s support and influence to all and sundry over the years. Majority of actors who venture into politics today do so because of the influence of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu. According to him, Tinubu is a bridge-builder across regional, ethnic and religious lines that is capable of uniting the country. “By God grace, Asiwaju will move from Jagaban of Borgu to Jagaban of Nigeria; from Asiwaju of Lagos to Asiwaju of Nigeria. For all your sacrifices, for all your effort, God will reward you this time. “If we look at the rotation of leadership in Nigeria over the years, it is very crystal clear It is Yoruba turn to be president”.